admin.ask:
How to approach classes. (Computer Science, General Education, etc.).
Experiences with Time Management. (Using a calendar system, Learning to say Yes/No).Technology: Oooh!
Using an editor such as vim or emacs. (This is important for remote development – when you are working on a machine that is not in the immediate vicinity).
Non-Technology:
How to adapt to large class sizes. (I came from a small high school).
How to utilize office hours efficiently. (What questions to ask, How to avoid peak-times).
admin.advice: One of my life mottos is to always “Keep Improving”. People, things, and goals change tremendously every five years. Learn to stay true to yourself and to seek out ways to overcome new challenges. Grades are important but not as important as sleep, meals, exercise, friends, family, and free time. I hope you will find the courage to find and practice your passion every day. A final note, it will all work out in the end. I don’t know how, but the pieces will all come together. Try new things. After all, failure is one of the best teachers.
